Johannesburg emergency workers are marching for their safety and well-being. eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu has the latest on the action. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Workers from Gauteng’s emergency medical services are accusing the health department of exploitation. They marched to the department's offices in Johannesburg on Thursday and handed over a memorandum, demanding payment for extra hours worked. READ: Attacks on Western Cape EMS staff highest in five years The department has been given two weeks to respond positively. Workers say if their concerns are not addressed, ambulances will not respond to emergency calls.